public class MainPanel
extends javax.swing.JPanel

Class to hold the main panel of the plugin. For the most part, designed using the form designer of NetBeans. Also contains logic to handle the two button press events.

doIdentifyActionPerformed

private void doIdentifyActionPerformed(java.awt.event.ActionEvent evt)
Clears the failure node list on the left of the main panel and re-fills it the the names of nodes that were determined to be failure nodes in the last calulation. Also prints out some basic statistics about the failure nodes in the panel header and selects the found nodes in the network view.

Parameters:
evt - The button press event. It is used solely to call this method.

doPlotActionPerformed

private void doPlotActionPerformed(java.awt.event.ActionEvent evt)
Used to sanitise text field input from the user and then calculate the average number of failure nodes from each run of the getFailureNodesWithRemoval() method and stores the result in an array that is then passed to the BoxDiagramPanel class to be used to draw the box plots.

Parameters:
evt - The button press event. It is used solely to call this method.
